criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Patients with cleft lip and palate;

          -  6 to 13 years before orthodontic treatment, with sagittal deficiency of the facial
             middle third;

          -  Angle Class III malocclusion, or mesial step of the deciduous second molars, and
             anterior crossbite;

          -  ANB less than 0˚, Wits less than -2 mm and the distance from point A to the
             perpendicular nasion less than 0 mm.

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  Previous orthodontic treatment;

          -  Other craniofacial anomalies;

          -  Inadequate maxillary denture for placement of a expander.
